[h1]RimTouch[/h1]

RimTouch adds an experimental direct touch input layer for RimWorld 1.6.

[h2]Features[/h2]
[list]
[*]UI tap repair for RimWorld buttons.
[*]One-finger local map pan.
[*]Hold-to-select drag box.
[*]Long-press right click/context actions.
[*]Double tap support.
[*]Two-finger pan and pinch zoom.
[*]World map touch pan and pinch zoom.
[*]Input suppression to reduce duplicate vanilla mouse/map behavior.
[*]Extended local map zoom range.
[*]UI scale list unlock up to 3.0x.
[/list]

[h2]Requirements[/h2]
[list]
[*]RimWorld 1.6
[*]Harmony
[/list]

[h2]Important Notes[/h2]
[list]
[*]Primary target: Windows touch devices such as Microsoft Surface tablets and laptops.
[*]Linux touch support is experimental and depends on Unity reporting touch input through the legacy input API.
[*]Camera, UI, input, and performance mods can affect gesture behavior. If touch panning feels wrong, test with only Harmony and RimTouch first.
[*]SimpleCameraSetting is not required. If you use it anyway, load RimTouch after it and test touch panning carefully.
[/list]

[h2]Reporting Issues[/h2]
Please include your device model, OS version, RimWorld version, full mod list, the exact gesture that failed, what you expected, what happened, and Player.log or HugsLib log if available.
